_üõ†Ô∏è Refactor suggestion_

**Consider making validation development-only**

The validation throws errors which could crash the game in production. The try-catch block just logs and rethrows, providing no safety net.


```diff
-    // Validate registry vs config in development builds
-    try {
-      this.validateSoundRegistry();
-    } catch (e) {
-      console.error(e);
-      throw e;
-    }
+    // Validate registry vs config in development builds only
+    if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development' || window.location.hostname === 'localhost') {
+      try {
+        this.validateSoundRegistry();
+      } catch (e) {
+        console.error('‚ö†Ô∏è Sound registry validation failed:', e.message);
+        // Don't throw in production - log and continue
+      }
+    }
```


